0.1 Packages

import Pkg; Pkg.add("PGFPlotsX")
using Plots
using PGFPlotsX
using LaTeXStrings
pkgversion(PGFPlotsX)
v"1.6.2"

1 Plot3

1.1 Coordinates

@pgf Axis(
    {
      xlabel=L"x",
      ylabel=L"y",
      zlabel=L"f(x,y)"
    },
    Plot3(
        {
            mark="*",
        },
        Coordinates(
          [(0,0,0)]
        )
    )
)

1.2 Table

x = [-4,    4,   4,   -4 ,-4]
y = [-5,   -5,   5,    5 ,-5]
z = -x/6 .+ y/2
@pgf Plot3(
    {
        mark="*",
    },
    Table(x, y, z)
    )

1.3 Expression

@pgf Axis(
    {
        xlabel = L"x",
        ylabel = L"y"
    },
    Plot3(
        Expression("-x/6+y/2")
    )
)

1.4 surf

x = range(-4; stop = 4, length = 20)
y = range(-5; stop = 5, length = 25)
f(x, y) = -x/6+y/2
@pgf Plot3(
    {
        surf,
    },
    Coordinates(x, y, f.(x, y'))
    )

1.5 backend

using Plots; 
pgfplotsx()
surface(range(-3,3, length=30), 
        range(-3,3, length=30),
        (x, y) -> x^2-y^2,
        label=L"x^2-y^2",
        colormap_name = "viridis")
